          <li><strong>Content production</strong> — 4–8 articles per month, briefs, optimisation, publishing.</li>
          <li><strong>On-page + technical</strong> — meta titles, internal links, schema, Core Web Vitals.</li>
          <li><strong>Local SEO</strong> — GBP posting, citations, review management, local pack tracking.</li>
          <li><strong>Reporting + strategy</strong> — monthly call, ranking report, keyword plan.</li>
        </ol>

        <div class="callout callout-warn">
          <div class="callout-label">⚠️ The retainer trap</div>
          <p>Most $3,000/mo SEO retainers spend 60% of the bill on account management, slide decks, and status calls. The actual deliverables — 6 articles and a GBP post a week — cost the agency less than $400 to produce. <strong>Autopilot tools cut the overhead and ship the same output for $100–$200/mo.</strong></p>
        </div>

        <h2 id="how-we-tested">How we tested all 10 alternatives</h2>
        <p>Same scope, same 90-day window, same three sites.</p>

